Pre-Game Insights: The Utah Jazz will travel to the Footprint Center to take on the Phoenix Suns.
The Jazz (9-27) have played better on the road so far this season and are surrendering a shade below 118 points per game.
Utah shot 40 percent from the field and committed 16 turnovers during a 97-92 home loss versus Miami.
Lauri Markkanen and Collin Sexton matched a game-high with 23 points on a combined 17-for-42 shooting effort.
Utah C Walker Kessler added nine points, 15 rebounds, and two blocks.
Kyle Filipowski secured 11 rebounds in 23 minutes off the Jazz bench.
The Phoenix Suns are three games above .500 at home and are a half-game behind San Antonio for tenth place in the Western Conference standings.
The Suns (17-19) rank tenth in the league in offensive efficiency and are scoring 112.1 points per contest.
On Thursday, Phoenix outscored Atlanta by ten points in the third quarter to pull away for a 123-115 home victory.
Bradley Beal led all scorers with 25 points (11-16 FG) and seven rebounds in 33 minutes off the Phoenix bench.
Kevin Durant and Grayson Allen scored 23 points apiece on a combined 16-for-23 from the field.
All-Star G Devin Booker added 20 points and 12 assists for the Suns.
Phoenix F Royce O’Neale is recovering from a left ankle sprain and will likely remain sidelined for this contest.
The Suns rank 24th in the league in defensive efficiency, which makes them hard to trust as a big favorite.
The Jazz rank last in the league in defensive efficiency, so take the over.
Final Score Prediction, Phoenix Suns win 124-113.
